headline: Azerbaijan's SOCAR signs oil exploration agreements with Exxon, BP
summary: BAKU (Reuters) -Azeri state energy company SOCAR signed new agreements for oil and gas exploration in Azerbaijan with Exxon Mobil and BP at an energy conference in Baku on Monday.  Azerbaijan has proven oil reserves of 7 billion barrels and proven natural gas reserves of 1.7 trillion cubic metres, according to the U.S. Department of Energy.  The country's oil output has been declining for several years after the Azeri–Chirag–Gunashli (ACG) complex of oilfields passed its peak of 50 million metric tons, or 1 million barrels per day, in 2010.
